description: Collaborated with some incredible people, amazing pod leader, and great mentor company, Major League Baseball.
Worked on a portfolio project, creating a reusable template for the future.
Used Python, Flask and Jinja, Bootstrap for styling
Implemented regular improvements to the UI/UX of our web application using 3rd-party software integrations for a customer-facing interface.
Developed, tested and maintained features creating reusable/modular code using Typescript, NextJS, ChakraUI, and MongoDB.

Given full-responsibility over large tasks (e.g. landing page), reaching out for consistent feedback, and making detailed reports on what I completed using media (video, photos, etc..) to supplement them.
Worked closely alongside a small dev team, having weekly meetings, 1:1's, and a clear line of communication throughout the development process.

experienceData.job_title: Vyper Protocol | Open Source Fellow | @ MLH Summer 2022 Batch
description: Tasked with creating an SDK to improve developer experience, implementing logic with Rust/Anchor and Typescript.
Contributed closely with the Project Maintainers to implement changes using well-tested code with Mocha.
Facilitated communication with pod-mates(team), maintainers, and the pod-leader(manager) with weekly meetings.

experienceData.job_title: Governance UI | Open Source Fellow | @ MLH Spring 2022 Batch
description: Took ownership in suggesting improvements to the UI/UX, streamlining the workflow of deployment.
Added features to the front end for on-chain spl-governance contract in order to create DAOs.
Developed, tested and maintained features using ES6 and Typescript.
